    <p>HeARTS In AC­Tion Vir­tual Event</p>
    <p>This two-day event cel­e­brates World Hos­pice and Pal­lia­tive Care Day, which falls on Oct 10. On the first day, there will be per­for­mances by artists, health­care work­ers and vol­un­teers, as well as con­ver­sa­tions on pal­lia­tive care. The sec­ond day will fea­ture a panel dis­cus­sion with pal­lia­tive care pro­fes­sion­als and two film screen­ings. The first is Os­carnom­i­nated doc­u­men­tary End Game (2018), about ter­mi­nally ill pa­tients in a San Fran­cisco hospi­tal seek­ing to change the per­cep­tion of life and death. The sec­ond screen­ing is The Sketch­book, a short film by event or­gan­iser Sin­ga­pore Hos­pice Coun­cil about an artis­tic boy suf­fer­ing from cancer who strikes up a friend­ship with a pal­lia­tive care nurse.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Oct 9, 8 - 9.15pm</p>
    <p>& Oct 10, 2.30 - 4.15pm</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free with reg­is­tra­tion INFO: www.sin­ga­pore­hos­pice.org.sg</p>


